Package: GGAligner
Title: BAM/SAM Read Aligner with Explicit CIGAR String Representation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Gabriele", "Gambero", , "gabriele.gambero@mail.polimi.it", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: GGAligner provides tools for aligning a specified read from BAM/SAM files to its reference genome using CIGAR strings. It allows for a clear representation of the alignment, including insertions, deletions, and mismatches. The package includes:
    - `ggbamloader`: Loads BAM/SAM files and returns a DataFrame (S4Vectors) for easier manipulation of reads.
    - `ggaligner`: Aligns a selected read from the DataFrame to the reference genome and provides a comparison of the aligned sequences.
